Much of religion of what ever sort, is a childish longing for a
supernatural parent figure.  In that primal instinctual awe  of the
universe it is mythologized, and worshiped in various way with many
different words and rites.

Some of the priestly class have had the leisure to discover usually
hidden capacities of the human animal that if they manifest at all,
usually do so only in moments of great crisis, where the human animal
seems almost capable of miracles.

Some argue that this state can be achieved intellectually as well as
spiritually.

But some people just want the social body of a nice nature friendly
religion, are not interested in the more esoteric aspects of a magico -
religious system, and thus we have types of Wicca that are almost
offensive in their superficiality.  But Magick, like every thing else is
based on understanding, being able to understand and not have immovable
blocks to it, thus being able to understand one can understand most things.

That does not mean one can explain or defend every thing, one almost
inevitably develop a sense of &quot;right&quot; and &quot;wrong&quot; for convenience sake
if nothing else.

In a perfect Universe, nothing is in error, but its a very difficult
premise to base a conversation on.
